# -*- mode: org -*-
#+title: gwwm - guile wayland windows mamager.

fork from dwl, add guile to configure it.

* WARN
Is a WIP project.
Both api changes and errors occur.
I don't use X11 app at basically, so I can't find some bugs about xwayland.

* how to build
you need
- automake
- autoconf
- bash
- guile
- [[https://github.com/Z572/guile-wayland][guile-wayland]]
- [[https://github.com/Z572/guile-wlroots][guile-wlroots]]
- pkg-config
- texinfo
- wlroots
- xorg-server-xwayland

#+begin_src sh
  autoreconf -fiv
  ./configure
  make -j
#+end_src

* develop
If you use emacs, you can use =geiser-connect= to connect gwwm.

If you use guix:
#+begin_src sh
  git clone gwwm
  git clone guile-wayland
  git clone guile-wlroots
  cd gwwm
  guix shell -D -f guix.scm
#+end_src

* configure
simple example
~/.config/gwwm/init.scm:
#+begin_src scheme
  (use-modules (gwwm)
               (gwwm config)
               (gwwm commands)
               (gwwm keymap)
               (gwwm hooks)
               (gwwm color))
  ;;; win+d
  (keymap-global-set (kbd (s d)) (lambda () (spawn "firefox")))
  (gwwm
   (borderpx 1)
   (sloppyfocus? #t)
   (xkb-rules
    (make-xkb-rules
     "us"
     #:model "asus_laptop"
     #:options
     '("ctrl:ralt_rctrl"
       "ctrl:swapcaps_hyper"
       "shift:both_capslock")))
   (bordercolor (make-color "#ffbbeeff")))

#+end_src


* thanks
Thanks of guile, dwl , tinywl ,sway.
